I wanted to fly since I was little.
And today it was so... Today I flew an airplane. I haven't quite processed that yet.
Data from Flightaware.
I try to go there again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's only Monday.
It's already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get the medical clearance due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will TAKE VERY long and means A LOT of extra work.
That's somewhat discouraging, but it's still just another problem that you have to solve. So far, it seems solvable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what's coming up for me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't let you get a medical clearance if you take medication for it.
